sentences.english: Unfortunately the person who usually sets up their expectation hasn't turned up.
sentences.chinese: 不幸地是，那个通常给他们安设期望值的人还没来。

sentences.english: And he shall set engines of war against thy walls, and with his axes he shall break down thy towers.
sentences.chinese: 他必安设撞城锤攻破你的墙垣，用铁器拆毁你的城楼。

sentences.english: And these are they whom David set over the service of song in the house of the LORD， after that the ark had rest.
sentences.chinese: 约柜安设之后，大卫派人在耶和华殿中管理歌唱的事。

sentences.english: The hydraulic cylinders are stored on the pile cap of the center landing.
sentences.chinese: 液压油缸安设在位于中心着陆的桩帽中。

sentences.english: At various locations along the reef, platforms were created to hold live rock.
sentences.chinese: 沿珊瑚礁的差别所在所搁放的台子儿被用来安设活石。

sentences.english: General Mills installed the sag correctors at Cedar Rapids.
sentences.chinese: 锡特拉皮兹市的通用磨粉公司就安设了骤降校正器。

sentences.english: In them hath he set a tabernacle for the sun
sentences.chinese: 神在其间为太阳安设帐幕。

sentences.english: This pipeline will haudio-videoestnosled on the No. 8 pipe rack .
sentences.chinese: 这条管线将安设于八号管廊架上。
